      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That's a valid fear - letting go can feel like resignation or surrender. But stopping the cycle of trying to fix things might just be the only way to free yourself from the emotional toll it's taking. It's a paradox - the only way to break free is to let go of the need to control or fix the situation. Sometimes, the only way to move forward is to acknowledge that you can't fix everything and that it's okay to let go.",
